statements.sql:
SELECT distinct
stores.*,
users_roles.role_id
FROM users AS stores
LEFT JOIN users AS storegroups ON (storegroups.id = stores.parent_id)
LEFT JOIN users AS resellers ON (resellers.id = storegroups.parent_id)
INNER JOIN users_roles ON users_roles.user_id = stores.id
WHERE users_roles.role_id != 0 AND (stores.parent_id = 7 OR storegroups.parent_id = 7 OR resellers.parent_id = 7)
hints: The != operator is not standard. Use the <> operator to test for inequality instead.

statements.sql:
SELECT count(devices.guid_) AS count
FROM users AS stores
LEFT JOIN users AS storegroups ON (storegroups.id = stores.parent_id)
LEFT JOIN users AS resellers ON (resellers.id = storegroups.parent_id)
INNER JOIN devices ON devices.store_guid_ = stores.store_guid
INNER JOIN users_roles ON users_roles.user_id = stores.id
WHERE users_roles.role_id = 4 AND (stores.parent_id = 7 OR storegroups.parent_id = 7 OR resellers.parent_id = 7)
